'''''Animal''''' is a non-fiction [[coffee table book]] edited by [[David Burnie]], who was the main-editor, and several co-authors. The full title of the book is: '''''Animal: The Definitive Visual Guide to The World's WildLife'''''. The 624-page book was published by [[Dorling Kindersley]] in 2001. The book is printed in full gloss paper and has numerous, full-color pictures.
The book is divided into several separate sections, each covering either a specific topic or a [[class (biology)|class]] of animals such as [[mammal]]s or [[reptile]]s. The introduction deals with how [[animal]]s are [[Taxonomic classification|classified]]. It also touches on [[ethology|animal behaviour]] and [[Biological life cycle|life cycle]]s. Later content delves into the [[Habitat (ecology)|habitat]]s of animals and how they live in them, [[Mammal]]s, [[Bird]]s, [[Reptile]]s, [[Amphibian]]s, [[Fish]], and [[Invertebrates]].
